Kayode Olusemire, the newly appointed Assistant Comptroller General of Nigerian Customs, was recently celebrated as his friends organized a reception for him at Ikoro-Ekiti, their home town, on January 7, 2022. President of his League of Friends, Chief Kayode Chubby Ajayi, used the occasion to express gratitude to President Muhammadu Buhari for appointing a distinguished son of the soil, Kayode Olusemire to serve in the top position within the Custom Service. In his message during the reception, Pastor Kayode Adeosun stated: “Members of the League of Friends, the High Chiefs of the Community and all our sons and daughters, both here at home and in the Diaspora are proud of you, Olusemire. Late Ogeh Was Intelligent Professional – Okowa SERAP Drags Lawan, Gbajabiamila To Court Over Failure To Explain… “You certainly deserve the recent promotion, having fastidiously worked in the Custom Service with total commitment and without any blemish, over the years. Indeed, you remain a worthy inspiration to us all and more so, the younger generation of Ikoro-Ekiti land. Let me add that all the members of the club wish you all the best in your new appointment”.